dshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","of Hampton Manor, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","of Hamton Manor, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Hampton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish: habitational name from any of numerous places called Hampton, including the cities of Southampton and Northampton (both of which were originally simply <i>Hamtun</i>). These all share the final Old English element <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’, but the first is variously <i>hām</i> ‘homestead’, <i>hamm</i> ‘water meadow’, or <i>hēan</i>, weak dative case (originally used after a preposition and article) of <i>hēah</i> ‘high’. This surname is also found in Ireland, having first been taken there in the medieval period.","History: The descendants of the clergyman Thomas Hampton, resident at Jamestown, VA, in 1630, lived in VA through three generations, multiplying their homesteads as the colony expanded and then branched into SC. This very common English name was brought independently to North America by many other bearers."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Stephen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Usual English spelling of the name of the first Christian martyr (Acts 6–7), whose feast is accordingly celebrated next after Christ's own (  26 December ). His name is derived from the Greek word <i>stephanos</i> ‘garland, crown’."],"variants":[{"name":"Stephan","meanings":["Variant of   Stephen  , preserving the vowels of the Greek name."]},{"name":"Steven","meanings":["Variant of   Stephen  , reflecting the normal pronunciation of the name in the English-speaking world."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Stephen de Hampton married Stephen de Hampton about 1249, in Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–1252":"–1252","1250–1268":"1250–1268","1252–1317":"1252–1317","–Female":"Surnud","1268":"1268","19 October 1252":"19. oktoober 1252","about 1249":"umbes 1249","19 October 1250":"19. oktoober 1250","1252":"1252","1250":"1250","1317":"1317","Of Hampton Manor, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","of Hampton Manor, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Hamton Manor, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–1252":"–1252","1250–1268":"1250–1268","1252–1317":"1252–1317","–Female":"Kuollut","1268":"1268","19 October 1252":"19. lokakuuta 1252","about 1249":"noin 1249","19 October 1250":"19. lokakuuta 1250","1252":"1252","1250":"1250","1317":"1317","Of Hampton Manor, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","of Hampton Manor, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Hamton Manor, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","–1252":"–1252","1250–1268":"1250–1268","1252–1317":"1252–1317","–Female":"Décédée","1268":"1268","19 October 1252":"19 octobre 1252","about 1249":"environ 1249","19 October 1250":"19 octobre 1250","1252":"1252","1250":"1250","1317":"1317","Of Hampt